  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to<strong> </strong>220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>chicken breast portion[s]</strong> and cook for 3 min on each side or until lightly browned, then remove from the heat</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/18-06-24_10h57m05s-APIC-1718879127863-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/18-06-24_10h57m05s-APIC-1718879127863-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/18-06-24_10h57m05s-APIC-1718879127863-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/18-06-24_10h57m05s-APIC-1718879127863-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/18-06-24_10h57m05s-APIC-1718879127863-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the<strong> browned chicken</strong> to a baking tray (use <strong>tin foil</strong> to avoid mess!)</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 12-14 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the juices run clear</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1638260184225-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1638260184225-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1638260184225-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1638260184225-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1638260184225-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the chicken is in the oven, peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 400ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[520ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[680ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1638260187375-x200.jpg",
